OL,5,Cthin'
OL,7,FZara confirmed that it had amended the
OL,8,Fproduct listings after receiving the
OL,9,Fcomplaint and removed the specific
OL,10,Fimages.
OL,12,FThe ASA said the low-cut design of the
OL,13,Fshirt in the first ad drew attention
OL,14,Fto the model's upper chest area,
OL,15,Fcreating a focal point around her
OL,16,Fcollarbone, which was protruding.
OL,18,FIn addition, the positioning of her
OL,19,Farms, while wearing a baggy shirt,
OL,20,Fcreated the impression that her arms,
OL,21,Fshoulders and chest were very slim.
